Text:
Woah! Look at all these people! This isn't some
third-rate tourist trap.

(These can't all be members of the faithful.
There are just too many people.)

(I suppose being in the middle of a trading city
makes it a pretty good sightseeing spot, too.)

(These historic buildings have a lot of tourist
appeal, just like Lindwurm.)
Hey there, miss, you on your lonesome?
And happy to stay that way.

Now, now, I'm not hitting on you! Look, see, I got
this here Church badge. I'm all official!
"Official Cathedral Advisor"? Looks shady...
Now, now! This's a real badge!
So, what do you want?

I'm 'ere to guide first-time tourists to our
cathedral—
Hard pass.
U-Um, miss?!
I'm not a pilgrim, got it? Bye, now!
O-Oh...

(I spotted almost 30 of those "Official Cathedral
Advisors" on the way in.)

(Heehee. Well, well, well. This might be sacred
ground, but people are people.)
(I suppose all tourist spots are the same.)

The sacred sermon is about to begin. Please, pay
heed in silence.
(And here comes the goddess talk.)
The sacred prophet!
Oh! She's a vision of sacred blessings!
We ask for silence as you heed the word.

(A vision of blessings, huh? Looks like simple magic
to me, though.)
Heehee...
Huh?!
(Did she just look at me...?)

(Nah, it was just a coincidence. There must be over
500 people in here.)

(But still, that was creepy. It's like I can't help
but possibly believe in this stuff...)
My name is Victoria.

As the incarnation of the will of Goddess Beatrix,
I will now share the Holy Teachings with you all.

I am truly grateful that once more, I can share the
word of the goddess with the faithful today.

(Ah, the legend of Goddess Beatrix blessing some
hero... More empty myths of praise.)

(I'm shocked it doesn't have the hero marrying some
princess like every generic fantasy story.)

And so heroic Olivier, bearer of the goddess's
blessing, stood against the demon Diablos.
(It's all fiction, the goddess and the hero both.)

(The only truth is the demon, and the cultists using
these myths to hide the existence of their master
Diablos.)

Olivier's sword overcame the fiend Diablos.
He severed the beast's left arm and sealed it.

(If the goddess were real, she would destroy the
Cult and truly save the world.)
Wha—?!
(Did she just look at me again?)

(Well, I have to admit that this "Prophet" certainly
knows how to dazzle people.)
(I wonder if I look at my lord like that?)

And that ends the prophetess's sermon today.
For all our pilgrims—

(Right, so now I very quietly pull back and mix with
the crowd until sundown.)
